article.headline: Texas A&amp,M 76, North Dakota 62
article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas -- Chinemelu Elonu scored 13 points and had 11 rebounds as Texas A&M defeated North Dakota 76-62 Monday night. Josh Carter scored a game-high 18 points for the Aggies (14-1). Donald Sloan and B.J. Holmes had 14 each. A&M, which led throughout, made 23 of 28 free throws. North Dakota (8-6) pulled within four at 37-33 three minutes into the second half on Derek Benter's 3-pointer. But Holmes responded with two 3-pointers over the next two minutes to shove the Aggies' lead back to double digits at 43-33. Following Benter's 3-pointer, the Aggies outscored the Fighting Sioux 19-5 over the next 10 minutes to put away their 10th consecutive victory. Travis Bledsoe led North Dakota with 13 points. The Aggies led by 14 with 3:46 remaining in the first half, but North Dakota outscored A&M 10-2 down the stretch to only trail 33-27 at halftime.
